				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$N=\frac{n}{s}d$$\end{document}

The stretching mechanism relies on a crank−slider design that converts rotational motion of the crank into linear motion of the slider, enabling smooth extension and retraction along the rail. Based on the geometric constraints of the crank−slider mechanism, the horizontal displacement x of the slider is given by Eq. 335:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
