				\begin{document}$$x(t)=r\cos \theta +\sqrt {{l^2} - {r^2}{{\sin }^2}\theta }$$\end{document}

The corresponding velocity v(t) and acceleration a(t) can be obtained as the first and second time derivatives of x(t) (Eqs. 4 and 5), respectively.4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
